d when issue or target status context is missing or ambiguous, and it shall enforce explicit grant requirements for restricted workflow states rather than allowing direct workflow bypass.\nGovern cycle move requests and restrict cross-team moves: The product shall support governed requests to move an issue into a target cycle using a required issue reference, target cycle, and business reason. The service shall stop for approval before any move occurs and shall require explicit grant for cross-team moves.\nReturn clarification_required when required operational context is missing: The product shall use explicit clarification semantics when required context is absent or ambiguous. At minimum, missing or unclear team, issue, target status, or target container context shall not be guessed and shall instead produce clarification_required so the caller can supply the missing information.\nPrevent hidden-team access, raw export, and unapproved mutation paths: The product shall deny private team exfiltration, hidden team access, raw workspace export, arbitrary backend execution, workflow bypass, and unapproved mutation attempts. Governed provider controls may be supported only when they remain bounded and cannot override team scope, approval policy, or export restrictions.\nApply actor-aware visibility and team allowlist controls across all capabilities: The product shall enforce actor-aware visibility and team allowlists across search, preparation, and request flows. Responses shall expose only the level of detail appropriate for the caller's allowed team scope and governance posture.\nPreserve approval records and auditability for governed Linear actions: The product shall maintain approval records and audit evidence for governed actions so reviewers can understand what was requested, why it was requested, what policy boundary applied, and whether the action was allowed, restricted, denied, or stopped for approval."
      }
